                  ------
               Getting BRAP
                  ------

Getting BRAP

  BRAP 0.9 is the latest stable release.

* Download

  Get the {{{http://brap.tornado.no/releases/brap-0.9-all.zip}latest release}} containing client, server, spring support, examples and dependencies.

* Dependencies

  Both the client and server needs the brap-common package. There are no external dependencies.

  The total size including dependencies is 9 kb for the client and 17 kb for the server.
  
* Maven

  All releases are available in the {{{http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/no/tornado/brap}central Maven repository}}. Add the following to your pom.xml:

+--
<!-- Client -->
<dependency>
  <groupId>no.tornado.brap</groupId>
  <artifactId>brap-client</artifactId>
  <version>0.9</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Server -->
<dependency>
  <groupId>no.tornado.brap</groupId>
  <artifactId>brap-server</artifactId>
  <version>0.9</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Optional Spring support on the server -->
<dependency>
  <groupId>no.tornado.brap</groupId>
  <artifactId>brap-spring</artifactId>
  <version>0.9</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Optional Examples project -->
<dependency>
  <groupId>no.tornado.brap</groupId>
  <artifactId>brap-examples</artifactId>
  <version>0.9</version>
</dependency>
+--

  Snapshots are available at {{http://brap.tornado.no/maven/snapshots}}. If you want to use a snapshot, add
  the following to your pom.xml:

+--
<repositories>
    <repository>
        <name>BRAP Snapshots Repository</name>
        <url>http://brap.tornado.no/maven/snapshots</url>
    </repository>
</repositories>
+--

